The New Africa Shrine on Wednesday announced a suspension of all its programmes as part of measures to curb the spread of COVID19. Femi, the son of Afrobeat legend, Fela Anikulapo-Kuti, disclosed this on his Twitter handle. According to the tweet, “The management of the New Africa Shrine has halted its regular programming as the country and the world at large continue to take precautionary measures against the spread of the Covid-19 pandemic.” Femi also advised everyone to stay safe, noting that they would continue to monitor the situation before the resumption of regular programming. 